Michael Hankinson will act as executive chairman in the transitional phase, supported by finance director Andrew Waller while the board embarks on a process to replace Olivier, who spent 31 years with the Durban-based group. Grindrod operates three divisions, freight services, shipping and financial services. The company suffered a net loss of R1.8bn in the year to December, up from a loss R1.3bn in the previous year. The share price was off marginally to R11.35 in mid-morning trade on the JSE, valuing the company at R8.7bn. Source: BDpro